{
  "pflowFormatVersion": 1,
  "workflow": {
    "name": "natebjones-delta",
    "description": "Incrementally update the 'NateBJones Prinzipien' research set: ingest new Substack posts and YouTube transcripts, run a delta analysis against the existing axiom/framework set, write a new update note, and propagate the changes into the core documents.",
    "args": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "requested_period": {
          "type": "string"
        },
        "work_root": {
          "type": "string",
          "default": "Intelligence Impact/INIM-RESEARCH/INIM-RESEARCH Work/NateBJones Prinzipien"
        },
        "inbox_folder": {
          "type": "string",
          "default": "Intelligence Impact/INIM-RESEARCH/INIM-RESEARCH Work/NateBJones Prinzipien/_inbox"
        },
        "substack_archive": {
          "type": "string",
          "default": "https://natesnewsletter.substack.com/archive?sort=new"
        },
        "youtube_channel": {
          "type": "string",
          "default": "https://www.youtube.com/@NateBJones/videos"
        },
        "substack_tier": {
          "type": "string",
          "default": "substack-paid (175€/Jahr-Tier)"
        },
        "on_exists": {
          "type": "string",
          "default": "version"
        }
      },
      "required": []
    }
  },
  "nodes": [
    {
      "id": "in",
      "kind": "input",
      "label": "Requested period",
      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": [
        {
          "id": "requested_period",
          "name": "requested_period",
          "schema": {
            "type": "string"
          }
        }
      ],
      "phase": "Input"
    },
    {
      "id": "corpus",
      "kind": "agent",
      "label": "Read corpus state",
      "prompt": "Read the NEWEST update note in work_root (the highest `0X …` number — determine it live, do not hard-code). It sets the increment boundary. Extract: corpus_state_raw (the raw `korpus-stand` range string, verbatim), increment_from (the END date of that range — the new increment's lower bound, exclusive), last_run (the `zuletzt-gelaufen` of `_src/prompts/natebjones-delta-update.md`; if it differs from increment_from, use the LATER of the two), last_update_note (filename of the newest note), next_update_number (newest + 1). Also verify today's date from <env> (never the knowledge cutoff) — the increment's upper bound. Consider the {{in:requested_period}} if one was given. Return all of these as the {{out:corpus_state}}.",
      "inputs": [
        {
          "id": "in:requested_period",
          "name": "requested_period",
          "schema": {
            "type": "string"
          }
        }
      ],
      "outputs": [
        {
          "id": "out:corpus_state",
          "name": "corpus_state",
          "schema": {
            "type": "string"
          }
        }
      ],
      "phase": "Read"
    },
    {
      "id": "scope",
      "kind": "agent",
      "label": "Confirm scope",
      "prompt": "Clarify scope with the user ONLY if {{in:requested_period}} is empty. Ask (AskUserQuestion) three things: period (default: from increment_from / the later of increment_from and last_run, to today), sources (default: Substack + YouTube), substack login path (default: Playwright with the existing session). Use the corpus state for the boundaries:\n\n{{in:corpus_state}}\n\nIf requested_period was set, derive period_from/period_to from it and take defaults for the rest without asking. Return period_from, period_to, sources, and login_path as the {{out:scope}}.",
      "inputs": [
        {
          "id": "in:requested_period",
          "name": "requested_period",
          "schema": {
            "type": "string"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "in:corpus_state",
          "name": "corpus_state",
          "schema": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "required": true
        }
      ],
      "outputs": [
        {
          "id": "out:scope",
          "name": "scope",
          "schema": {
            "type": "string"
          }
        }
      ],
      "phase": "Scope"
    },
    {
      "id": "precond",
      "kind": "loop",
      "label": "Preconditions",
      "prompt": "Verify the Substack paid session before fetching, given the scope:\n\n{{in:scope}}\n\nUsing Playwright (mcp__playwright__browser_*), open any paid post and check the full text appears. If the session is logged out (paid posts truncated / 'Subscribe to read'): have the user log in via a `! ` command — NEVER ask for tokens — then this step retries with {{in:retry}}. On the FIRST line emit exactly `SESSION: ready` once the full text is visible as the {{out:session_ready}}, otherwise `SESSION: blocked` (the user login is still pending).",
      "inputs": [
        {
          "id": "in:scope",
          "name": "scope",
          "schema": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "required": true
        },
        {
          "id": "in:retry",
          "name": "retry",
          "schema": {
            "type": "string"
          }
        }
      ],
      "outputs": [
        {
          "id": "out:session_ready",
          "name": "session_ready",
          "schema": {
            "type": "string"
          }
        }
      ],
      "phase": "Preconditions",
      "config": {
        "maxPasses": 5,
        "sentinel": "SESSION:\\s*ready"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "ss-fetch",
      "kind": "agent",
      "label": "Substack fetch",
      "prompt": "Fetch the Substack corpus — only NEW posts since increment_from (within the clarified period). Proceed only once the session is ready:\n\n{{in:session_ready}}\n\nLoad the archive (substack_archive); after browser_navigate wait briefly then browser_evaluate WITHOUT clicks (the page re-navigates on interaction). Filter to Nate's own posts (a[href*=\"natesnewsletter.substack.com/p/\"]). Pull reliable dates from the footer 'recent posts' block of an opened post (format `MMM DD • NATE`), NOT the archive DOM (which has audio lengths like '46:36' that misparse as dates). For each new post pull the full text via `div.available-content`. Collect each post as { url, slug, title, date, body, paywalled_flag } and return them as the {{out:substack_posts}}.",
      "inputs": [
        {
          "id": "in:session_ready",
          "name": "session_ready",
          "schema": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "required": true
        }
      ],
      "outputs": [
        {
          "id": "out:substack_posts",
          "name": "substack_posts",
          "schema": {
            "type": "string"
          }
        }
      ],
      "phase": "Substack"
    },
    {
      "id": "ss-classify",
      "kind": "agent",
      "label": "Substack classify",
      "prompt": "Classify each post as full text or teaser (the paywall heuristic), given the fetched posts:\n\n{{in:substack_posts}}\n\nFull-text posts are ~15k–32k chars; Executive-Briefing teasers are ~2.5k–4.5k chars and end with 'Executive Circle members enjoy…' (the non-active AI Executive Circle tier). Set an `access` field per post: `full` (complete) or `teaser` (mark as [PAYWALL-TEASER]; the body may later be filled from the matching YouTube transcript). Return the posts with the access field as the {{out:substack_posts_classified}}. If all new posts are teasers or there are none, that is valid — the run continues with YouTube.",
      "inputs": [
        {
          "id": "in:substack_posts",
          "name": "substack_posts",
          "schema": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "required": true
        }
      ],
      "outputs": [
        {
          "id": "out:substack_posts_classified",
          "name": "substack_posts_classified",
          "schema": {
            "type": "string"
          }
        }
      ],
      "phase": "Substack"
    },
    {
      "id": "ss-inbox",
      "kind": "agent",
      "label": "Substack inbox",
      "prompt": "Write each classified post as its OWN raw file into inbox_folder, given:\n\n{{in:substack_posts_classified}}\n\nFormat EXACTLY like the existing `_inbox/` files (frontmatter quelle/titel/autor/datum/zugriff/abgerufen/tags, then `# title` and body). Append ` — NUR TEASER, Volltext im AI Executive Circle Tier` to `zugriff` when access is teaser, and mark a teaser body as [PAYWALL-TEASER]. Collect the written paths — these are the provenance anchors the update note will wikilink, so filenames must match exactly. Return the {{out:substack_inbox_files}} paths.",
      "inputs": [
        {
          "id": "in:substack_posts_classified",
          "name": "substack_posts_classified",
          "schema": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "required": true
        }
      ],
      "outputs": [
        {
          "id": "out:substack_inbox_files",
          "name": "substack_inbox_files",
          "schema": {
            "type": "string"
          }
        }
      ],
      "phase": "Substack"
    },
    {
      "id": "yt-fetch",
      "kind": "agent",
      "label": "YouTube fetch",
      "prompt": "Fetch the YouTube corpus — BINDING USER RULE: always base each evaluation on the VIDEO TRANSCRIPT, not just the description. Proceed only once the session is ready:\n\n{{in:session_ready}}\n\nOpen youtube_channel (dismiss the DE consent wall with 'Alle ablehnen' if shown). Read the video list from ytInitialData (richGridRenderer → lockupViewModel: contentId, title, metadata rows). The English original title is in videoDetails.title of the watch page. Keep only new videos vs increment_from. Get each transcript via the DOM panel (the timedtext API returns empty for ASR captions): open the watch page, click the transcript button, wait ~2s, read the EXPANDED engagement-panel text (filtering search-box, timestamps `^\\d+:\\d+$`, and `N Sekunden/Minuten` markers). Collect each as { id, title_en, date, views, transcript } and return them as the {{out:youtube_videos}}.",
      "inputs": [
        {
          "id": "in:session_ready",
          "name": "session_ready",
          "schema": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "required": true
        }
      ],
      "outputs": [
        {
          "id": "out:youtube_videos",
          "name": "youtube_videos",
          "schema": {
            "type": "string"
          }
        }
      ],
      "phase": "YouTube"
    },
    {
      "id": "yt-map",
      "kind": "agent",
      "label": "YouTube map",
      "prompt": "Map each video to one of three categories by comparing the fetched videos:\n\n{{in:youtube_videos}}\n\nwith the classified Substack posts:\n\n{{in:substack_posts_classified}}\n\nThe three categories: post-pendant (a video version of a same-named post → 1:1 pair in video_post_map), standalone (no post pendant → extra content from the transcript), or paywall-filler (a video whose post is access: teaser → its transcript fills the missing full text). This three-way split steers the next step: pendants and standalones go into the collected YouTube inbox file; paywall-filler transcripts are additionally appended to the matching teaser inbox file. Return video_post_map, standalone_videos, and paywall_fillers as the {{out:youtube_mapping}}.",
      "inputs": [
        {
          "id": "in:youtube_videos",
          "name": "youtube_videos",
          "schema": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "required": true
        },
        {
          "id": "in:substack_posts_classified",
          "name": "substack_posts_classified",
          "schema": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "required": true
        }
      ],
      "outputs": [
        {
          "id": "out:youtube_mapping",
          "name": "youtube_mapping",
          "schema": {
            "type": "string"
          }
        }
      ],
      "phase": "YouTube"
    },
    {
      "id": "yt-inbox",
      "kind": "agent",
      "label": "YouTube inbox",
      "prompt": "Save the YouTube findings as ONE collected inbox file plus targeted appends, given the mapping:\n\n{{in:youtube_mapping}}\n\nWrite `YYYY-MM-DD–DD YouTube-Korpus ….md` into inbox_folder containing: the video↔post mapping table, standalone extra content, and the paywall-fill list. Frontmatter like the Substack inbox files; quelle = channel URL. Additionally append paywall-filling video transcripts to the matching teaser inbox file in the Substack inbox files:\n\n{{in:substack_inbox_files}}\n\n(under a `## Volltext aus YouTube-Transkript` heading) so the teaser counts as filled — this requires the Substack inbox files to already exist (that is why this step is wired after Substack inbox). Return the {{out:youtube_inbox_file}}.",
      "inputs": [
        {
          "id": "in:youtube_mapping",
          "name": "youtube_mapping",
          "schema": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "required": true
        },
        {
          "id": "in:substack_inbox_files",
          "name": "substack_inbox_files",
          "schema": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "required": true
        }
      ],
      "outputs": [
        {
          "id": "out:youtube_inbox_file",
          "name": "youtube_inbox_file",
          "schema": {
            "type": "string"
          }
        }
      ],
      "phase": "YouTube"
    },
    {
      "id": "existing",
      "kind": "agent",
      "label": "Read existing set",
      "prompt": "Read the FULL existing set so numbering continues without gaps, scoped by the corpus state:\n\n{{in:corpus_state}}\n\nFrom `01 Mindset-Axiome.md` (plus the additions in the update notes): all axioms A1…An — note the highest number. From `06 Beratungs-Frameworks.md` plus the framework registers of the update notes: all frameworks F1…Fn — note the highest number. From the newest update note: the open research gaps / observation points (some mature into axioms over runs). Return axioms, frameworks, and gap_notes as the {{out:existing_set}} — the reference every new contribution is checked against.",
      "inputs": [
        {
          "id": "in:corpus_state",
          "name": "corpus_state",
          "schema": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "required": true
        }
      ],
      "outputs": [
        {
          "id": "out:existing_set",
          "name": "existing_set",
          "schema": {
            "type": "string"
          }
        }
      ],
      "phase": "Existing"
    },
    {
      "id": "delta",
      "kind": "synthesize",
      "label": "Delta analysis",
      "prompt": "Delta analysis — the analytical core. Check each new contribution against the existing set, given the Substack inbox files:\n\n{{in:substack_inbox_files}}\n\nthe YouTube inbox file:\n\n{{in:youtube_inbox_file}}\n\nand the existing set:\n\n{{in:existing_set}}\n\nClassify per contribution: new axiom? (only if a core conviction recurs across sources and is not covered → A{n+1}); refinement? (an existing axiom gets a supplementary paragraph → note `→ Wirkt auf [[01 Mindset-Axiome#A{n}]]`); new framework? (→ F{n+1}); observation point? (research gaps). Form 2–3 thematic arcs; quote verbatim with source + date; prepare an impact table (which core docs get what, with status). Return new_axioms, refinements, new_frameworks, observation_points, thematic_arcs, and the impact_table as the {{out:delta}}.",
      "inputs": [
        {
          "id": "in:substack_inbox_files",
          "name": "substack_inbox_files",
          "schema": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "required": true
        },
        {
          "id": "in:youtube_inbox_file",
          "name": "youtube_inbox_file",
          "schema": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "required": true
        },
        {
          "id": "in:existing_set",
          "name": "existing_set",
          "schema": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "required": true
        }
      ],
      "outputs": [
        {
          "id": "out:delta",
          "name": "delta",
          "schema": {
            "type": "string"
          }
        }
      ],
      "phase": "Delta"
    },
    {
      "id": "format",
      "kind": "agent",
      "label": "Format update",
      "prompt": "Render the new update note in the style of `09 / 10 / 11 Update … — Delta-Auswertung`, using the corpus state:\n\n{{in:corpus_state}}\n\nand the delta analysis:\n\n{{in:delta}}\n\nSet update_filename to `{{next_update_number}} Update {{today}} — Delta-Auswertung.md`. Advance the increment boundary: set the new `korpus-stand` to `\"{{increment_from}} bis {{today}}\"` — the range THIS run covered (never a single date, or the next run loses its start bound). Fill the template (frontmatter with tags/status/erstellt/parent/korpus-stand/zugriffsstand/quelle-roh; an intro blockquote citing the previous note and corpus state; then sections: TL;DR delta, Neuzugänge table, Thematische Bögen, Neue Axiome, Verfeinerungen, Neue Frameworks, Wirkungstabelle, Forschungslücken, Quellen). Output ONLY the rendered note as the {{out:formatted}} body.",
      "inputs": [
        {
          "id": "in:corpus_state",
          "name": "corpus_state",
          "schema": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "required": true
        },
        {
          "id": "in:delta",
          "name": "delta",
          "schema": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "required": true
        }
      ],
      "outputs": [
        {
          "id": "out:formatted",
          "name": "formatted",
          "schema": {
            "type": "string"
          }
        }
      ],
      "phase": "Format"
    },
    {
      "id": "save",
      "kind": "agent",
      "label": "Save update",
      "prompt": "Save the rendered update note via write_note. Write the formatted body:\n\n{{in:formatted}}\n\nto work_root, named by update_filename (`{{next_update_number}} Update {{today}} — Delta-Auswertung.md`). Honour on_exists if the target exists. Return the final written path as the {{out:saved_path}}.",
      "inputs": [
        {
          "id": "in:formatted",
          "name": "formatted",
          "schema": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "required": true
        }
      ],
      "outputs": [
        {
          "id": "out:saved_path",
          "name": "saved_path",
          "schema": {
            "type": "string"
          }
        }
      ],
      "phase": "Save"
    },
    {
      "id": "propagate",
      "kind": "loop",
      "label": "Propagate docs",
      "prompt": "Propagate the changes into the existing core documents — ONE impact_table row per pass, until all are done. Use the delta:\n\n{{in:delta}}\n\nand the saved update note path:\n\n{{in:saved_path}}\n\nPer row, update the addressed document (`01 Mindset-Axiome`, `06 Beratungs-Frameworks`, `00 INDEX`, others 02–05/07 only if required). Set each row's status to `erledigt` or `offen-optional`. On the FIRST line emit `ALL_ROWS_DONE: yes` when every row is done as the {{out:impact_done}}, otherwise `ALL_ROWS_DONE: no` and proceed to the next row (continuing on {{in:retry}}). The loop is bounded: one row per pass.",
      "inputs": [
        {
          "id": "in:delta",
          "name": "delta",
          "schema": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "required": true
        },
        {
          "id": "in:saved_path",
          "name": "saved_path",
          "schema": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "required": true
        },
        {
          "id": "in:retry",
          "name": "retry",
          "schema": {
            "type": "string"
          }
        }
      ],
      "outputs": [
        {
          "id": "out:impact_done",
          "name": "impact_done",
          "schema": {
            "type": "string"
          }
        }
      ],
      "phase": "Propagate",
      "config": {
        "maxPasses": 12,
        "sentinel": "ALL_ROWS_DONE:\\s*yes"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "cleanup",
      "kind": "agent",
      "label": "Cleanup",
      "prompt": "Finish & hygiene, once propagation is done:\n\n{{in:impact_done}}\n\nMANDATORY increment markers (or the next run evaluates wrong): set `zuletzt-gelaufen` in `_src/prompts/natebjones-delta-update.md` to today (the next default run reads it as the 'since last run' lower bound); consistency-check that `zuletzt-gelaufen` (= today) matches the end date of the new `korpus-stand` — both should point to the same state. Hygiene: delete all scratch files (`post-*.txt`, `yt-*.txt`, temp scripts) in the vault root (do NOT touch `.playwright-mcp/`); verify the update note (at {{in:saved_path}}) has wikilinks matching the real `_inbox/` filenames exactly; if Substack/YouTube DOM selectors changed, fix them in the template AND in the fetch steps of this workflow. Return the {{out:cleanup_done}} = ok.",
      "inputs": [
        {
          "id": "in:impact_done",
          "name": "impact_done",
          "schema": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "required": true
        },
        {
          "id": "in:saved_path",
          "name": "saved_path",
          "schema": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "required": true
        }
      ],
      "outputs": [
        {
          "id": "out:cleanup_done",
          "name": "cleanup_done",
          "schema": {
            "type": "string"
          }
        }
      ],
      "phase": "Cleanup"
    },
    {
      "id": "end",
      "kind": "output",
      "label": "Done",
      "inputs": [
        {
          "id": "in",
          "name": "cleanup_done",
          "schema": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "required": true
        }
      ],
      "outputs": [],
      "phase": "Done"
    }
  ],
  "wires": [
    {
      "from": {
        "nodeId": "in",
        "portId": "requested_period"
      },
      "to": {
        "nodeId": "corpus",
        "portId": "in:requested_period"
      }
    },
    {
      "from": {
        "nodeId": "in",
        "portId": "requested_period"
      },
      "to": {
        "nodeId": "scope",
        "portId": "in:requested_period"
      }
    },
    {
      "from": {
        "nodeId": "corpus",
        "portId": "out:corpus_state"
      },
      "to": {
        "nodeId": "scope",
        "portId": "in:corpus_state"
      }
    },
    {
      "from": {
        "nodeId": "scope",
        "portId": "out:scope"
      },
      "to": {
        "nodeId": "precond",
        "portId": "in:scope"
      }
    },
    {
      "from": {
        "nodeId": "precond",
        "portId": "out:session_ready"
      },
      "to": {
        "nodeId": "precond",
        "portId": "in:retry"
      }
    },
    {
      "from": {
        "nodeId": "precond",
        "portId": "out:session_ready"
      },
      "to": {
        "nodeId": "ss-fetch",
        "portId": "in:session_ready"
      }
    },
    {
      "from": {
        "nodeId": "ss-fetch",
        "portId": "out:substack_posts"
      },
      "to": {
        "nodeId": "ss-classify",
        "portId": "in:substack_posts"
      }
    },
    {
      "from": {
        "nodeId": "ss-classify",
        "portId": "out:substack_posts_classified"
      },
      "to": {
        "nodeId": "ss-inbox",
        "portId": "in:substack_posts_classified"
      }
    },
    {
      "from": {
        "nodeId": "precond",
        "portId": "out:session_ready"
      },
      "to": {
        "nodeId": "yt-fetch",
        "portId": "in:session_ready"
      }
    },
    {
      "from": {
        "nodeId": "yt-fetch",
        "portId": "out:youtube_videos"
      },
      "to": {
        "nodeId": "yt-map",
        "portId": "in:youtube_videos"
      }
    },
    {
      "from": {
        "nodeId": "ss-classify",
        "portId": "out:substack_posts_classified"
      },
      "to": {
        "nodeId": "yt-map",
        "portId": "in:substack_posts_classified"
      }
    },
    {
      "from": {
        "nodeId": "yt-map",
        "portId": "out:youtube_mapping"
      },
      "to": {
        "nodeId": "yt-inbox",
        "portId": "in:youtube_mapping"
      }
    },
    {
      "from": {
        "nodeId": "ss-inbox",
        "portId": "out:substack_inbox_files"
      },
      "to": {
        "nodeId": "yt-inbox",
        "portId": "in:substack_inbox_files"
      }
    },
    {
      "from": {
        "nodeId": "corpus",
        "portId": "out:corpus_state"
      },
      "to": {
        "nodeId": "existing",
        "portId": "in:corpus_state"
      }
    },
    {
      "from": {
        "nodeId": "ss-inbox",
        "portId": "out:substack_inbox_files"
      },
      "to": {
        "nodeId": "delta",
        "portId": "in:substack_inbox_files"
      }
    },
